I have a problem with my screenshots. One thing I noticed is that the first screen is not showing the right number of rows. It is showing the first row of the table. 
How do I fix this? 
Thanks in advance.

A:

The first row of the table is being displayed as a new row. You don't want to display the new row in the first row.
Use the following in your code:
   this.row = table.displayRow(row)

This will display all the rows of the table as a new row.

Q:

How to run a test script on my PHP server?

I am trying to run a test script on my PHP server. I am using this code:
<?php
if (isset($_SERVER['PHP_SELF']) && $_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] == 'GET' && $_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'] == "http://a.xyz.com") {
    $input = preg_replace('/[a-zA-Z]/', '', $input);
    echo '<script type="text/javascript" src="http://a.xyz.com/script.js"></script>';
    $result = $script = "";
    $result = $script = "script.php";
    $result = $script = "";
    $result = $script = "";
    $result = $script = "";
    echo '<script type="text/javascript" src="http://a.xyz.com/script.js"></script>';
}
else {
    $script = "script.php";
    echo '<script type="text/javascript" src="http://a.xyz.com/script.js"></script>';
}
?>

Is this possible?

A:

You need to use the "script.php" and the "script.php" files to do the same thing.
You could use the same approach to execute the scripts.php and the "script.php" files. They will be executed only when you add the scripts.php file to the "scripts.php" file.
php script.php file_get_contents("script.php");

php script.php file_put_contents("script.php");

